The paper discusses privacy risks associated with GANs and proposes a taxonomy of membership inference attacks against GANs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of computer security (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on privacy and attacks, cs.CR is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant due to the use of GANs and the analysis of their effectiveness in different application scenarios.
